        <infon key="n">2</infon>
        <offset>52</offset>
        <text>Dissolved oxygen concentration is a crucial organizing principle in marine ecosystems.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">3</infon>
        <offset>139</offset>
        <text>As oxygen levels decline, energy is increasingly diverted away from higher trophic levels into microbial metabolism, leading to loss of fixed nitrogen and to production of greenhouse gases, including nitrous oxide and methane.
</text>
