      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">4</infon>
        <offset>366</offset>
        <text>In this Review, we describe current efforts to explore the fundamental factors that control the ecological and microbial biodiversity in oxygen-starved regions of the ocean, termed oxygen minimum zones.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">5</infon>
        <offset>569</offset>
        <text>We also discuss how recent advances in microbial ecology have provided information about the potential interactions in distributed co-occurrence and metabolic networks in oxygen minimum zones, and we provide new insights into coupled biogeochemical processes in the ocean.
</text>
